<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-46-0020 </DOCNO><TEXT>An attempt is made to understand time translational invariance as a purelyformal symmetry. The idea is that even if time translational invarianceis broken in the basic quantum mechanical Hamiltonian, one can anywayrewrite the physical model in a time translational invariant manner.One may argue that it is this kind of a formal invariance that is seenexperimentally.</TEXT></DOC>